        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 2:50PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 250 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Downtown Concord, or near Mt Pleasant, moving east
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Downtown Concord and Mt Pleasant.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
